quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  72,1,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “It was revealed to me that a band of unseen beings{1}listened in and said, ‘Indeed, we have heard a wondrous Recital{2}",footnotes:1:The Arabic word used is jinnwhich are unseen beings that are accountable for their actions.|2:The Arabic word used is Qur’anwhich literally means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.
  72,2,"that guides to prudence, so we have come to believe in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord."
  72,3,"<span class=""h"">And that<sup foot_note=""81379"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>most high is the Grandeur of our Lord—He never took a female companion nor a child."
  72,4,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>our fool used to speak untruthfully about Allah."
  72,5,"<span class=""h"">And that<sup foot_note=""81380"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>we thought that humans and unseen beings would never <span class=""h"">say<sup foot_note=""81381"" class=""qiraat"">2</sup> </span><span class=""h"">a lie about</span>Allah."
  72,6,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>d </sup></a>certain men among humans used to seek refuge in certain men among the unseen beings, but they only increased them in confusion."
  72,7,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>they thought, as you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>thought, that Allah would never resurrect anyone."
  72,8,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we sought to reach the heaven and found it filled with stern guards and meteors."
  72,9,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we used to take up positions to listen in, but whoever listens now finds a meteor in wait for him."
  72,10,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>we do not know whether ill has been desired for those on earth, or if their Lord has desired prudence for them."
  72,11,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>some of us are righteous, but some of us are less than that: we have been following divergent roads."
  72,12,"<span class=""h"">And that<sup foot_note=""81382"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>we realized that we cannot thwart Allah on earth, nor can we thwart Him by fleeing."
  72,13,"<span class=""h"">And that</span><a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>when we heard the guidance we believed in it, for whoever believes in his Lord fears neither loss nor confusion."
